result.name: Wing Hong Dessert

reviews.text: A small dessert shop sells Chinese sweet soup. There are many choices including red bean soup, mung bean soup and yuba sweet soup with eggs ( 腐竹鷄旦糖水 ). The quality is good. Price is reasonable. A bowl of sweet soup sold for HK$17. It attracts a lot of customers to visit. The shop is small, there are not many seats offered. Sometimes, it is difficult to find a seat. For this reason, many people buy takeaways at this dessert shop.

I had the bitter "turtle jelly" and my wife got some simple porridge. Both were very delicious and satisfying. I was very happy with our snack. There was no menu in English, but the staff does speak English. Due to the customer traffic they were a bit busy, but friendly none-the-less.
There are better options nearby.
Not very good quality.
Nice dessert
